# Line endings are LF, everywhere, including on Windows checkouts (RUN-42).
#
# Not a preference — a correctness requirement, and CI proved it: Windows defaults
# `core.autocrlf=true`, so every file checked out with CRLF and biome (which mandates LF)
# flagged the entire repo, starting with biome.json itself. The lint step cannot pass on a
# Windows runner without this.
#
# `text=auto eol=lf` normalizes to LF in the index and checks LF out on every platform. Modern
# Windows tooling — including Git for Windows, PowerShell, and Node — handles LF fine; the
# CRLF default is a compatibility hangover, and letting it win here would mean either a
# Windows-only lint failure forever or a formatter config that disagrees with itself per OS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary, so git never guesses at line endings inside them.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
